Stereotypes
[[Image:Blackguyliedetector.jpg|thumb|145px|This black person is having his biological reaction to a [[chicken|test substance]] recorded]]
A stereotype is [[scientology|scientifically]] [[fact|proven fact]] that applies to a certain black person or [[feminazi|group]]. For something to have stereotype status, it most go through months of vigorous laboratory testing. The studies and their results are well scrutinized by [[TOW|biologists, psychologists and sociologists]], meaning that all stereotypes in use today are undeniably [[truth|true]]. Despite all the solid scientific backing supporting stereotypes, some people are still [[RAGE|intensely]] [[butthurt|offended]] by their use. 

= Origin of Stereotypes =
Stereotypes normally start when the stupidity of another race comes to the attention of the more [[whites|perceptive and intelligent members of a society]]. Slowly but surely, the quality of the race or group becomes more and more known.  The target of the stereotype then gets [[butthurt|upset]] that their dark secret is revealed. 

